 often visit due to chronic aches and pains. <br \\/>Volunteers for this medical project come from diverse backgrounds all over Malaysia and Singapore, and they work hand in hand with the diligent volunteers from Sai Ananda Foundation. Everyone who joins in is reminded before every camp that compassion for suffering and love for everyone irrespective of race religion position or nationality are the only necessary ingredients to make this service project a success.<\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"b819658\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"content_width\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":700,\"sizes\":[]}},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"3ab318c\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"51742da\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"title\":\"Why did we form this portal?\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"heading\"},{\"id\":\"e239411\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false}]'),
