(26, 1, '2020-09-08 03:37:48', '2020-09-08 03:37:48', '<h2>“Rather, ten times, die in the surf, heralding the way to a new world, than stand idly on the shore” <br/>- Florence Nightingale</h2>		\n				0\n							REGULAR VILLAGES ADOPTED \n				0\n							PATIENTS SEEN TILL DATE WITH REGULAR FOLLOW UP CAMPS \n				0\n							PATIENTS SCREENED PER MEDICAL CAMP \n				0\n							SPECIALITIES OFFERED \n										<img width=\"800\" height=\"400\" src=\"http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/dc-pic01-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/dc-pic01-1.jpg 800w, http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/dc-pic01-1-300x150.jpg 300w, http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/dc-pic01-1-768x384.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" />											\n		<h2><strong>Aim and Vision</strong></h2><p><strong>Doctors Connect Foundation Malaysia</strong>’s sole aim is in creating access for quality healthcare to remote inaccessible and poor socio-economic areas to provide quality medical screening and care for the needy and unfortunate irrespective of race, religion or nationality – all <strong>FREE</strong> of cost!</p><p>Our vision is unity in diversity - breaking boundaries of race religion and nationality and seeing one in all. Our mission is to provide free, high quality, and compassionate medical care to the underprivileged communities in Malaysia who have poor access to healthcare. </p>		\n			<h2>Our Future Plans</h2>		\n		  <ul>\n	    		      		<li>                                                        	      		 Healthcare awareness</li>\n	      		      		<li>                                                        	      		 Ophthalmology</li>\n	      		      		<li>                                                        	      		 Mobile pathology</li>\n	      		      		<li>                                                        	      		 Ultrasound services</li>\n	      	    		</ul>\n		      												<h5>Systematic health talks will be conducted in batches for all patients who visit medical camps, with the sole purpose of uplifting health awareness</h5>							    			\n		      												<h5>To get a team of ophthalmologists to help assess and screen patients with diabetic retinopathy, glaucoma, cataract and refractions, and engage in education and early intervention. Future equipment: A slit lamp.</h5>							    			\n		      												<h5>A portable laboratory to provide value in our screening and help detect nutritional anaemias, chronic infections, renal diseases, cholesterol issues and complications of lifestyle disease. Once detected, emphasis is on education and early intervention. Future equipment: A mobile lab.</h5>							    			\n		      												<h5>To help provide quality screening for rural villagers for gynaecology diseases, as well as pregnant mothers, and ensure that that women’s health in rural areas are not neglected due to lack of education or poor socioeconomic conditions. Future equipment: A portable ultrasound machine.</h5>							    			\n				<img src=\"http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Kerling-pic06.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Kerling-pic06.jpg\" alt=\"\"><h4>Kerling – Mobile Medical Camp – 7 October 2018</h4><a href=\"http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Kerling-pic06.jpg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"no\">\n            </a><a href=\"#\"></a>\n				<img src=\"http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Kerling-pic17-2.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Kerling-pic17-2.jpg\" alt=\"\"><h4>Kerling – Mobile Medical Camp – 16 December 2018</h4><a href=\"http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Kerling-pic17-2.jpg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"no\">\n            </a><a href=\"#\"></a>\n				<img src=\"http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Dengkil-pic03.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Dengkil-pic03.jpg\" alt=\"\"><h4>Dengkil – Orang Asli – Mobile Medical Camp – 13 January 2019</h4><a href=\"http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Dengkil-pic03.jpg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"no\">\n            </a><a href=\"#\"></a>            \n                <article data-id=\"72\">\n                            <header><h2><a\n                href=\"http://localhost/A2/2020/09/08/kerling-mobile-medical-camp-7-october-2018/\"\n                title=\"Kerling – Mobile Medical Camp – 7 October 2018\"\n                >Kerling – Mobile Medical Camp – 7 October 2018</a></h2></header><a href=\"http://localhost/A2/author/u7vacs2ym4znb/\" title=\"Posts by MartinLee\" rel=\"author\">MartinLee</a><time datetime=\"08/09/2020\">08/09/2020</time>\n                <p>Kerling is a &nbsp;small town in Hulu Selangor, famous for...</p><a\n                    href=\"http://localhost/A2/2020/09/08/kerling-mobile-medical-camp-7-october-2018/\"\n                    >Read More</a>\n                    </article>\n			<a href=\"#\" role=\"button\">\n						More Posts\n					</a>\n			<h2>Our journey</h2>		\n			<a\n                    href=\"#/\"  \n                    style=\"background-image: url(http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Kerling-pic01-1.jpg);\"\n                >\n                                <h2>Our journey</h2>\n                                <p></p>\n		          </a><a\n                    href=\"#/\"  \n                    style=\"background-image: url(http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Kerling-pic02-1.jpg);\"\n                >\n                                <h2>Our journey</h2>\n                                <p></p>\n		          </a><a\n                    href=\"#/\"  \n                    style=\"background-image: url(http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Kerling-pic15-1.jpg);\"\n                >\n                                <h2>Our journey</h2>\n                                <p></p>\n		          </a><style typr=\"