5>Systematic health talks will be conducted in batches for all patients who visit medical camps, with the sole purpose of uplifting health awareness</h5>							    			\n		      												<h5>To get a team of ophthalmologists to help assess and screen patients with diabetic retinopathy, glaucoma, cataract and refractions, and engage in education and early intervention. Future equipment: A slit lamp.</h5>							    			\n		      												<h5>A portable laboratory to provide value in our screening and help detect nutritional anaemias, chronic infections, renal diseases, cholesterol issues and complications of lifestyle disease. Once detected, emphasis is on education and early intervention. Future equipment: A mobile lab.</h5>							    			\n		      												<h5>To help provide quality screening for rural villagers for gynaecology diseases, as well as pregnant mothers, and ensure that that women’s health in rural areas are not neglected due to lack of education or poor socioeconomic conditions. Future equipment: A portable ultrasound machine.</h5>							    			\n				<img src=\"http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Kerling-pic06.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Kerling-pic06.jpg\" alt=\"\"><h4>Kerling – Mobile Medical Camp – 7 October 2018</h4><a href=\"http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Kerling-pic06.jpg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"no\">\n            </a><a href=\"#\"></a>\n				<img src=\"http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Kerling-pic17-2.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Kerling-pic17-2.jpg\" alt=\"\"><h4>Kerling – Mobile Medical Camp – 16 December 2018</h4><a href=\"http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Kerling-pic17-2.jpg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"no\">\n            </a><a href=\"#\"></a>\n				<img src=\"http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Dengkil-pic03.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/A2/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Deng